SIMPLE: lurcher
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lurcher
<hw>Lurch"er</hw> <pr>(l⟦ucir⟧rch"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Lurch</er> to lurk.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One that lurches or lies
in wait; one who watches to pilfer, or to betray or entrap; one who
lurks; a lurker; a poacher.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a mongrel breed of dogs
said to have been a cross between the sheep dog, greyhound, and spaniel.
It hunts game silently, by scent, and is often used by
poachers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lurcher</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lurcher
<hw>Lurch"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lurco</ets>,
<ets>lurcho</ets>, a glutton. See 1st <er>Lurch</er>.]</ety> <def>A
glutton; a gormandizer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lurchline</ent>⟦br⟧
